bokov's oeuvre and to explore how art deepens the potency of the prominent themes threaded throughout his work. The authors trace the role of art in Nabokov's life, from his alphabetic chromesthesia-a psychological condition in which letters evoke specific colors-to his training under Marc Chagall's painting instructor to his deep admiration for Leonardo da Vinci and Hieronymus Bosch. They then examine over 150 references to specific works of art in such novels as Laughter in the Dark, The Real Life of Sebastian Knight, Pnin, Lolita, Ada, and Pale Fire and consider how such references reveal new emotional aspects of Nabokov's fiction. A fascinating and wholly original study, Nabokov and the Art of Painting will be invaluable reading for scholars and enthusiasts of Nabokov alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPainting in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAshenden, Liana, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBarbara, Santa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, D. Barton, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVoorschoten, D. Barton Johnson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVries, Gerard de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048505463zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048505463423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048505463.jpg  a978-3-11-070067-1  AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-a